My meme

My meme is about a perplexed monkey. It can be used anytime youre assigned a task but you have no clue what its about.

I added suitable text to these images, tailored to their characteristics, and in the meme, I pieced them together. I adjusted the sizes, selecting prominent fonts and colors.

library(magick)
you_image <- image_read("https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/previews/012/721/532/original/awkward-look-monkey-puppet-icon-free-vector.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(200)%>%
  image_annotate(text = "You?",
                 color = "yellow",
                 size = 48,
                 font = "mono",
                 gravity = "south")

huh_image <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/4jkbsq.png")%>%
  image_scale(200)%>%
  image_annotate(text = "Huh...",
                 color = "yellow",
                 size = 48,
                 font = "mono",
                 gravity = "south")

me_image <- image_read("https://cdn170.picsart.com/upscale-228465789059212.png?r1024x1024")%>%
  image_scale(200)%>%
  image_annotate(text = "Me?",
                 color = "yellow",
                 size = 48,
                 font = "mono",
                 gravity = "south")
what_image <- image_read("https://ih0.redbubble.net/image.4741986117.8515/raf,360x360,075,t,fafafa:ca443f4786.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(200)%>%
  image_annotate(text = "What?",
                 color = "yellow",
                 size = 48,
                 font = "mono",
                 gravity = "south")

first_line <- c(you_image) %>%
  image_append()

second_line <- c(huh_image) %>%
  image_append()

third_line <- c(me_image) %>%
  image_append()

final_line <- c(what_image) %>%
  image_append()

c(first_line, second_line, third_line,final_line) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)%>%
  image_write("my_meme.png")

gif_frames <- c(you_frame1,you_frame2,you_frame3, huh_frame1,huh_frame2,huh_frame3,me_frame1,me_frame2,me_frame3,what_frame1,what_frame2,what_frame3)

#run it, change the fps make it faster
image_animate(gif_frames, fps = 2)%>%
  image_write("my_animation.gif")

Creativity

I adjusted the speed of the GIFs because I believed that 2 seconds suited my project better than 1 second, and I also re-arranged the sequence of the animations. For each one, I want to show more shocking effect. So, I gradually increased the text size on the same images in the animation. I used some CSS to alter the appearance of the HTML, making them look more engaging.

Learning reflection

In Module 1, I learned how to create an emoji pack using R, which is incredible. It demonstrates the power of modern technology. I want to explore CSS design further because Ive discovered that although CSS seems simple, it can create many vibrant web pages. Additionally, Im interested in delving deeper into fonts within the emoji pack, such as studying font backgrounds and styles.
